The paper deals with the problem of estimating the learnability of a model class from a small amount of data, which is a fundamental problem in machine learning. The paper presents results for both regression and binary classification problems, which are common topics in the machine learning literature. The paper also discusses the sample complexity of the proposed methods, which is a key concern in statistical learning theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.STAT (Statistics), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
